Ihave also allowed the fact of an honorable hanishment into Egypt, though not the cause assigned by the Gram- marians (the supposed attack on the pantomimo Paris), which is impossible. That Juvenal did not professedly - composa satira till late in lise, is admitted and accounted for. Likewise that he may have written verses before he ventured to publish them, and that some of these were afterwards incorporated with his Satires, is allowed. Itis also admitted that he attended the usual schools in early life, and practised rhetoric till middle age. chond these facts tho Grammarians, I believe, have been misled.
